benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: Valid Request: Happy path (TC01) verifies 200 and JSON array with matching externalKey.

Query Parameters: extensive coverage of externalKey, includedDeleted (true/false), audit (FULL/MINIMAL/NONE), invalid values, empty value, and extra/unsupported params (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC09, TC10, TC15, TC29).
Error Handling: Non-existent key and empty DB -> 404 (TC08, TC16); missing required parameter -> 400 (TC07); invalid params -> 400 (TC09/TC10).
Authorization: Unauthorized (401) and insufficient-permissions (403) tests included (TC11, TC12).
Soft Delete Semantics: includedDeleted true/false behavior covered, including deleted-flag expectations (TC02, TC06).
Audit Levels: FULL/MINIMAL/NONE behavior covered (TC03, TC04, TC05).
Service/Dependency Failures: database/service unavailable and service downtime covered with 503 expectations (TC13, TC28).
Security: SQL injection and XSS input handling tests included (TC19, TC20).
Concurrency & Load: concurrent requests and high-volume DB tests present (TC18, TC27), and a large-duplicate-payload scenario (TC14).
Boundary & Encoding: non-ASCII, max/min length, and unexpected input formats covered (TC23, TC24, TC25, TC26).
Performance: basic response-time SLA test included (TC17).
Response Shape/Schema: Content-Type checked and required Bundle fields validated (TC01, TC30).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination parameters (limit/offset/page), page size, or Link/next/prev headers for large result sets (even though large-dataset scenarios exist, pagination-specific behavior is not verified).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No scenarios exercise repetitive/rapid requests to validate throttling behavior or 429 responses and Retry-After semantics.
Caching Behavior / Conditional GET: No tests for ETag, Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional GETs (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) and 304 handling.
Detailed header expectations: aside from Content-Type, tests do not assert other important headers (Cache-Control, ETag, Vary, Content-Length, or any API-version headers).

Pagination-related performance: while large DB and concurrency are tested, there are no tests validating performance/behavior when results would be paginated (e.g., ensuring consistent ordering across pages).
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include limit/offset/page parameters, verify returned page sizes, ordering, Link headers (next/prev), and behavior when requesting pages beyond available data.
Add rate-limiting tests: send burst requests to validate 429 responses, ensure Retry-After header is present and honored, and verify idempotency/behavior under throttling.

Add caching / conditional GET tests: assert presence of Cache-Control/ETag/Last-Modified, test If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to validate 304 responses and ensure no sensitive info is returned on conditional failures.
Expand header assertions: include checks for Cache-Control, ETag, Vary, Content-Length, and any API-version headers to ensure consistent API behavior.

Add tests for malformed authentication (expired/revoked tokens) and token scopes to complement 401/403 tests, and add schema validation tests that assert types and optional vs required fields explicitly (beyond presence).
